Day 13: Indexes & Query Optimisation

Topic:
Indexes and SQL Query Optimisation

Learning Objectives:

Understand what indexes are and why they are used in databases
Learn the difference between clustered and non-clustered indexes
Understand how indexes improve query performance
Learn how to create indexes using SQL commands
Explore the basics of the EXPLAIN statement for query analysis

Activities / Deliverables:

Add indexes to important tables in VolyoDB
Run queries before and after indexing
Use EXPLAIN to analyse query execution plans
Compare query performance and note cost changes
Document observations on how indexing affects speed and efficiency

Tools / Tech:

MySQL 8
EXPLAIN Statement

